20
00:01:33,370 --> 00:01:35,650
Wait, isn't this for two people?

21
00:01:35,650 --> 00:01:38,510
My cooking yielded enough for two.

22
00:01:38,510 --> 00:01:41,000
If you do not require it...

23
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,360
I shall feed it to the cat downstairs.

24
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,990
No, I'll take it.

25
00:01:44,990 --> 00:01:46,690
Thank you.

26
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,720
I've been wondering.

27
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:59,570
Why didn't you just cook for yourself if you're good at it?

28
00:01:59,570 --> 00:02:03,090
I previously believed cooking was the wife's job.

29
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:06,680
Thinking back on it, I should've cooked my own meals.

30
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,360
What a late revelation.

31
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,760
I, too, have had something on my mind.

32
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:14,020
You are quite terrible at eating fish.

33
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,920
Really?

34
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,890
You go in...

35
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,540
And pull it out, like so.

36
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:24,900
Wow, how unnecessarily clean!

37
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,480
"Unnecessarily?"

38
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:30,350
<i>It's easier to live as acquaintances.</i>

39
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:32,190
<i>I wonder why?</i>

40
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,850
As for my future plans,

41
00:02:35,850 --> 00:02:39,820
I will move to my family home in Mito, as soon as possible.

42
00:02:39,820 --> 00:02:41,250
Is that so?

43
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:47,240
Speaking of, our realtor told me they found someone interested in this house

44
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:50,540
and that they'd like to inspect the place.

45
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:54,590
- <i>Woohoo, we're here to inspect!</i>
- <i>Inspection time!</i>

46
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:56,980
Are they allowed to film?

47
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:58,530
Woah!

48
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:01,990
I don't recall giving filming permission.

49
00:03:01,990 --> 00:03:05,040
- Isn't this curtain weird?
-  Can sunlight even filter through?

50
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:08,130
It's not like anyone would target us from outside!

51
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:09,630
One cannot remain unguarded.

52
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:13,530
- Danger lurks in the most unexpected of places!
- What?

53
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:14,760
Sorry.

54
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:17,260
Can't imagine us living here.

55
00:03:17,260 --> 00:03:19,870
- Family rules?
- Lame.

56
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:22,970
What was up with those people?

57
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:26,570
"Looks old, bad taste, it's a compromise."

58
00:03:26,570 --> 00:03:28,750
Who says that about someone else's home? Rude.

59
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,200
Would you rather not?

60
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,260
What?

61
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:33,170
That is, sell this house.

62
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:35,930
No, I'd prefer we sell it.

63
00:03:38,330 --> 00:03:40,370
Yes, Obara speaking.

64
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:44,080
Really?

65
00:03:45,130 --> 00:03:49,010
The rude people from earlier would like to buy this place.

66
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,810
Shall I move forth with that?

67
00:03:53,630 --> 00:03:55,190
Or is that a no?

68
00:03:55,190 --> 00:03:56,540
Not at all.

69
00:03:56,540 --> 00:03:59,500
I was just surprised because it was so sudden.

70
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:02,560
I'm glad there's a buyer. Let's go for it.

71
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,510
Understood.

72
00:04:04,510 --> 00:04:06,060
Thank you for waiting.

73
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,460
Yes, please give them the details.

74
00:04:08,460 --> 00:04:10,500
Thank you very much!

75
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,930
They wish to sign the agreement in two weeks, on Saturday.

76
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:17,490
- Is that all right?
- Yeah, I'll leave my plans open.

77
00:04:18,910 --> 00:04:24,600
I shall... leave the day before everything is signed

78
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:28,510
and move back to my family home.

79
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:30,080
I see.

80
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:37,390
Koichi, on the day you leave,

81
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:41,130
why don't we eat dinner together?

82
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:44,010
- Huh?
- It'll be our "Last Supper".

83
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:47,690
I'll do my best and cook.

84
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,930
Really?

85
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:56,780
I'll look... forward to it.

86
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:04,810
Nine o'clock.

87
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:06,070
Three o'clock.

88
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,770
- Private Tani!
- Good day!

89
00:05:07,770 --> 00:05:09,400
- No more cast?
- No.

90
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,220
- I'm all healed.
- Way to go, man!

91
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:14,400
Let us exercise to celebrate Private Tani's recovery!

92
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,640
- Yes, sir!
- Ready and...

93
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:21,370
- One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight!
- One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight!

94
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:26,890
What's that document?
<i>[Change of Address Form]</i>

95
00:05:32,370 --> 00:05:36,510
To tell you the truth, I plan on returning to my hometown of Mito.

96
00:05:38,010 --> 00:05:41,440
Will your wife accompany you?

97
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:45,200
I apologize for meddling.

98
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,210
No worries.

99
00:05:47,210 --> 00:05:51,000
I hear you visited my wife the other day?

100
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,460
What I did was out of line!

101
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:57,210
Not at all.

102
00:05:57,210 --> 00:06:01,860
Thank you very much for worrying about me.

103
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,170
<i>My deepest apologies!</i>

104
00:06:05,170 --> 00:06:08,630
It's rude enough for you to fall asleep on me on call,

105
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:11,190
but I had to get scolded by your husband too?

106
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:14,200
I'm terribly sorry.

107
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:18,840
From now onwards, I'll dedicate my all to work without further distractions.

108
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,520
Then do you have any innovative new ideas

109
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,300
for a novel?

110
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:26,630
Don't tell me you came with nothing?

111
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:32,400
How about a story about family?

112
00:06:33,030 --> 00:06:36,950
Two complete strangers meet,

113
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,320
get married, and become family.

114
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:43,780
However, they won't necessarily stay together forever.

115
00:06:44,810 --> 00:06:47,650
I got the idea from my parents.

116
00:06:47,650 --> 00:06:49,650
Some people don't have a family.

117
00:06:49,650 --> 00:06:52,930
That's... true,

118
00:06:52,930 --> 00:06:56,250
but maybe they'll meet someone and become family.

119
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,480
Sorry, I'll bring a new idea-

120
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,300
Let's say, for example,

121
00:07:01,210 --> 00:07:05,090
there's a child who was abandoned by their parents.

122
00:07:05,090 --> 00:07:06,940
They were raised at an orphanage,

123
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:10,340
grows up and become a successful entrepreneur.

124
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,480
Maybe...

125
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:16,900
our protagonist is a man who sells love.

126
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:19,110
So a man who doesn't understand love,

127
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:21,690
desires love, sells love,

128
00:07:21,690 --> 00:07:23,530
and thus comes to understand love?

129
00:07:23,530 --> 00:07:25,210
Exactly.

130
00:07:25,210 --> 00:07:29,350
Whether or not he becomes family with someone is still unknown, though.

131
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:32,180
I think that's a wonderful idea!

132
00:07:35,050 --> 00:07:39,150
- Hey, where do you think you are?
- Stand up.

133
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:41,270
You should not remove me by force.

134
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:43,070
- What?
- Pardon me!

135
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:46,370
- Aoyama!
- He's no suspicious individual.

136
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,610
Are you all right?

137
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,820
There's something I wish to discuss.

138
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:54,280
Okay.

139
00:08:06,690 --> 00:08:08,820
What is it?

140
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:11,560
I'm not exactly free.

141
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,590
I hear you're getting a divorce.

142
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:17,810
Let me help you since that's my field of expertise.

143
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:23,590
The house loan and the wages you have both accrued while married will be part of the distribution of property.

144
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:25,920
- Additionally-
- Stop that.

145
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:29,880
I don't want to talk about this.

146
00:08:32,170 --> 00:08:34,440
Obara asked me to do this.

147
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,430
<i>Would you...</i>

148
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:41,430
<i>please be Saki's consultant?</i>

149
00:08:41,430 --> 00:08:43,690
<i>I put her in your care.</i>

150
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,730
Koichi asked?

151
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:51,000
Obara... is a good person,

152
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:54,310
but isn't that why he's suffering?

153
00:08:54,990 --> 00:08:58,580
He's an upright person, raised in an upright family.

154
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:01,290
So he himself believes he must also be respectable.

155
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,910
Didn't you feel pressured

156
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:06,740
by the assumed responsibilities of a "wife"?

157
00:09:09,180 --> 00:09:13,240
Saki, you only need to remain true to yourself.

158
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:16,120
At least, that's what I believe.

159
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,500
I'm home!

160
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,550
Welcome back.

161
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:31,110
- Did you eat?
- Yeah.

162
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:35,390
I bought extra, so feel free to eat it for breakfast tomorrow.

163
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:39,870
Will you return to your family home...

164
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:42,820
after moving out?

165
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:46,380
I guess so.

166
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:48,800
Koichi, is there anything you'd like to take?

167
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:52,700
Since you chose all the furniture, feel free to take it all.

168
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:55,020
Not everything will fit back home.

169
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:58,780
In that case, should we have a company pick them up?

170
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:00,910
Let's see.

171
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:03,240
There's a sofa, a bed...
<i>[Rinacchi]</i>

172
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:06,260
"Rinacchi?"

173
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:09,500
Who is Rinacchi?

174
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:10,970
W-Well...

175
00:10:10,970 --> 00:10:14,360
<i>Rinacchi is just a friend. Nothing more!</i>

176
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,870
That's confidential.

177
00:10:15,870 --> 00:10:18,030
No way, were you <i>cheating</i>?

178
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:19,920
O-Of course not!

179
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,950
You're so frantic, it's suspicious.

180
00:10:21,950 --> 00:10:23,440
This is the second secret now!

181
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,850
No, this is your father's-

182
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:27,370
Dad?

183
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,350
My Dad's what?

184
00:10:29,350 --> 00:10:30,590
His other woman?

185
00:10:30,590 --> 00:10:32,410
U-Um...

186
00:10:32,410 --> 00:10:34,680
His friend?

187
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:39,360
- H-His...
- Koichi, give me the details!

188
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:44,490
<i>[How to Get a Divorce for the Whole Family]</i>

189
00:10:44,490 --> 00:10:46,570
<i>[Episode 6]</i>

190
00:10:47,390 --> 00:10:49,060
What now?

191
00:10:49,060 --> 00:10:51,920
We're having Takaya deal with the divorce.

192
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,940
It was my idea.

193
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:57,940
I wanted you two to talk it out, without a lawyer.

194
00:10:57,940 --> 00:11:00,000
Azusa, go play a game.

195
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,660
Okay.

196
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:04,700
We have nothing to talk about.

197
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:08,160
I've already made my decision.

198
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:11,050
Now, now, let's not be hasty.

199
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:13,690
What about your clothes and belongings?

200
00:11:13,690 --> 00:11:15,120
It's fine with me if you take them all.

201
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:18,020
Same with all the brand-name bags and jewelry I've given you.

202
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:20,460
Even the bed and dresser were made-to-order.

203
00:11:20,460 --> 00:11:23,230
And I don't need any of that. Besides...

204
00:11:23,230 --> 00:11:25,160
Besides?

205
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,520
It's nothing.

206
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:31,590
I only want one thing. You know that, right?

207
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:37,090
You're only reaping what you sowed.

208
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:39,900
Though you gave  gifts to Mom,

209
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:44,030
you gave them to other women too.

210
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:46,060
This is...

211
00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:49,340
my final gift to you.

212
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,880
<i>[Divorce Forms]</i>

213
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:55,740
"Thank you. This is the best present I've gotten from you."

214
00:11:55,740 --> 00:11:58,370
Hey! Were you eavesdropping, again?

215
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:01,250
I only said exactly what Ms. Midori thought.

216
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:03,520
How observant of you!

217
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,650
I thought my inner voice leaked out!

218
00:12:05,650 --> 00:12:07,690
Right?

219
00:12:07,690 --> 00:12:09,090
You're so harsh.

220
00:12:09,090 --> 00:12:11,950
Well, I'm making the taxi wait.

221
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:15,830
Bye-bye.

222
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:17,670
Mom!

223
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:21,850
Are you okay with this?

224
00:12:21,850 --> 00:12:23,330
There's nothing I can do.

225
00:12:23,330 --> 00:12:27,340
Once she's set her mind on something, she won't listen.

226
00:12:27,340 --> 00:12:30,190
You don't know that.

227
00:12:30,190 --> 00:12:32,990
Maybe deep down inside, she's conflicted.

228
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:36,550
Maybe she's waiting for you to call it off!

229
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:38,240
Saki?

230
00:12:43,770 --> 00:12:45,790
Mom!

231
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:47,330
Saki?

232
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:49,840
Are you "really" okay with this?

233
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:53,790
I don't think divorce is a bad thing.

234
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:58,210
After all, I'm getting a divorce to move forth.

235
00:12:58,210 --> 00:13:01,550
Plus, it's just as possible to get a divorce because you care.

236
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,460
Just kidding!

237
00:13:12,610 --> 00:13:15,560
- Midori!
- Tachikawa?

238
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:18,510
You came for me!

239
00:13:18,510 --> 00:13:20,920
I wanted to hurry and see you, Midori.

240
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:23,820
After your divorce is finalized, I want to tell you something.

241
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:25,840
What is it? Tell me now!

242
00:13:27,310 --> 00:13:30,080
I'm serious about you!

243
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,980
Please consider me, not only as your work partner,

244
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:36,070
but your partner in private as well.

245
00:13:36,990 --> 00:13:39,030
That makes me so happy!

246
00:13:39,690 --> 00:13:41,430
Let's celebrate today.

247
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:44,100
I already booked a restaurant.

248
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:52,470
<i>[Mammography Exam Results]</i>

249
00:13:53,630 --> 00:13:55,380
What's wrong?

250
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:57,630
It's nothing!

251
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:59,620
Let's go.

252
00:14:00,670 --> 00:14:03,300
- Thank you!
- No, thank you!

253
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,300
Pardon us.

254
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:07,130
Take care!

255
00:14:08,070 --> 00:14:09,650
Thank you for contacting me.

256
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:13,350
I hear... you will be returning to Hakone?

257
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:15,280
Indeed.

258
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:18,200
I finally finished packing everything!

259
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:24,620
Your father... signed the form.

260
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:30,160
<i> [Divorce Papers]</i>

261
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:36,690
With this... I can live life on my own two legs,

262
00:14:36,690 --> 00:14:40,080
as one human being.

263
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:43,780
Thank you very much.

264
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,230
Dear...

265
00:14:51,330 --> 00:14:55,240
No, you're no longer my "Dear".

